@Node ProcurePPC

powerpc.library/ProcurePPC                          powerpc.library/ProcurePPC

    NAME
        ProcurePPC - bid for a semaphore (V15)

    CPU
        PowerPC

    SYNOPSIS
        ProcurePPC(_PowerPCBase, SignalSemaphorePPC, SemaphoreMessage)
                   r3            r4                  r5

        void ProcurePPC(struct Library *,
                        struct SignalSemaphorePPC *, struct SemaphoreMessage *);

    FUNCTION
        Allows to obtain semaphores asynchronously and allows to wait
        for multiple semaphores at once. This is the mirror function of
        exec/Procure. See the documentation of exec/Procure for more
        infos.

        Note, that ProcurePPC is implemented according to exec V39/V40
        behaviour of Procure.

    INPUTS
        _PowerPCBase - base of powerpc.library
        SignalSemaphorePPC - pointer to a signalsemaphorePPC structure
        bidMessage- SemaphoreMessage that you wish replied when
                you obtain access to the semaphore.  The message's
                ssm_Semaphore field will point at the semaphore that
                was obtained.  If the ssm_Semaphore field is NULL,
                the Procure() was aborted via Vacate.
                The mn_ReplyPort field of the message must point to
                a valid message port.
                To obtain a shared semaphore, the ln_Name field
                must be set to 1.  For an exclusive lock, the ln_Name
                field must be 0.  No other values are valid.

    SEE ALSO
        @{"VacatePPC" link VacatePPC}, @{"powerpc/semaphoresPPC.h" link "include:powerpc/semaphoresPPC.h/Main" 7}

@EndNode

