@Node TrySemaphorePPC

powerpc.library/TrySemaphorePPC                powerpc.library/TrySemaphorePPC

    NAME
        TrySemaphorePPC - gain exclusive access to a semaphore with timeout (V15)

    CPU
        PowerPC

    SYNOPSIS
        status = TrySemaphorePPC(_PowerPCBase, SignalSemaphorePPC, Timeout)
                                 r3            r4                  r5

        LONG TrySemaphorePPC(struct Library *,
                                struct SignalSemaphorePPC *, ULONG);

    FUNCTION
        Tries to get exclusive access to a signal semaphore. If the semaphore
        is occupied, the task adds itself into a waiting queue. The task
        only waits for the amount of time given with the 'Timeout' parameter.
        If the semaphore couldn't be obtained during this time, the
        function returns.

    INPUTS
        _PowerPCBase - base of powerpc.library
        SignalSemaphorePPC - pointer to a signalsemaphorePPC structure
        Timeout - timeout value in microseconds

    RESULT
        status - status value:
            ATTEMPT_SUCCESS: operation successful
            ATTEMPT_FAILURE: semaphore couldn't be locked

    NOTES
        This call is guaranteed to preserve all GPR (except r0/r3)
        and the CTR.

    SEE ALSO
        @{"InitSemaphorePPC" link InitSemaphorePPC}, @{"FreeSemaphorePPC" link FreeSemaphorePPC}, @{"AttemptSemaphorePPC" link AttemptSemaphorePPC},
        @{"ReleaseSemaphorePPC" link ReleaseSemaphorePPC}, @{"AddSemaphorePPC" link AddSemaphorePPC}, @{"RemSemaphorePPC" link RemSemaphorePPC}
        @{"FindSemaphorePPC" link FindSemaphorePPC}, @{"ObtainSemaphorePPC" link ObtainSemaphorePPC}, @{"powerpc/semaphoresPPC.i" link "include:powerpc/semaphoresPPC.i/Main" 18},
        @{"powerpc/semaphoresPPC.h" link "include:powerpc/semaphoresPPC.h/Main" 9}

@EndNode

